data.description: This amazing split level plan is open and full of natural light. Recently updated and offering over 2200 square feet of finished living area per seller ( some sq ft not listed on assessors site) 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, Upstairs open kitchen with center island and pantry, dining area, large primary suite, the four season room has a beautiful view overlooking the back yard and into green space.  The finished lower level hosts three bedrooms one could be used as an additional family room, 3/4 bath. The home also hosts a large 2 stall garage. Convenient to all the Waukee Schools, the interstate, and multiple parks/trails. Features of the home include: Newer carpet, Washer new 2022 and Dryer new 2018, large deck, mature trees, New HVAC 2018. This location is hard to beat and is just a few minutes walk to Sugar Creek Golf Course, Centennial Park, and the Raccoon River Valley Trail!  All information obtained from Seller and public records.
